posts.name: Paul Rensing
posts.cooked:

The camera locations seem wrong. “Right” is a tiny bit forward and on the left, and “Left” is in the back right.

Cameras look like this. they are angle inwards at about 35 degrees and up at about 10 degrees.

posts.name: Paul Rensing
posts.cooked:
So, as others already said, your locations are incorrect based on the photo (I assume those on are on the “Front” of the robot).

But also, the Yaw angles (turn inward) are backward. Yaw is right-handed with your thumb pointing up, so your left camera is yawed negative 35 degrees and the right is yawed positive 35.  This will definitely screw up the results.

So, to fix the code you posted earlier, I think it should be:

That should get you close, but as you already noticed, since you have the cameras tilted, you really should be doing this in 3d all the way to the end, and then stripping it down to 2d.

You can use the example from JohnFogarty, or you can see our code here: ReefScape2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/AprilTagVision.java at main · ligerbots/ReefScape2025 · GitHub

One word of caution however: 3D rotations are a really pain to specify correctly. The exact way they are written, in particular, the order that the angles are applied makes a difference, and can be hard to debug. What we use for the camera Rotation3d is (Java, and using your numbers):

So, pitch the camera up by 10 degrees (yes, a tilt up is a negative angle), followed by a yaw of 35 degrees. Don’t just put the yaw angle in the third argument.

Hope this helps and good luck. Happy to keep helping.
